From 3e67bbc90c9c25cf27ee58d0e15f86c4c6b9ca4f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 12:42:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: 5-palette deterministic color pick + governed icon
 registry + text-to-diagram drills
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Color (no randomness — the human picks once, every build reads it):
- themes/palette-{navy,red,blue,green}: four CONTRAST-lint-calibrated presets
  (accent dark enough for white text; accentDeep/surfaceA >= 4.5; warn
  distinct from accent in the red palette). Fifth choice = オリジナル via
  theme-init's guided build (day1-deck's navy x gold is the worked example).
- theme-init Step 0 (new): the 5-way quick-pick; chosen file copied to the
  project's theme.json + one line in DESIGN.md. project-scaffold offers it
  right after scaffolding. Design stays out of CLAUDE.md (M-5/M-6).

Icons (role markers, never decoration — M-8):
- bin/graphics/icons.js: 13 hand-drawn mono line pictograms (person/people/
  company/bank/document/coin/house/car/shield/heart/calendar/target/chart),
  theme-ink colorized at build, embedded as SVG data URIs.
- system nodes accept {label, icon} (registry name OR the project's own SVG
  path — the existing iconSlot contract); sysNodeSpec is the single source
  the builder draws with and the height gate measures with.
- design-lint ICON: unknown names hard-error (no clipart drift); engine
  skips missing files gracefully (adversarial: must not throw).
- references/graphics/icon-catalog.md: the selection rules (actor/object
  only, exclusive meaning, registry-or-path, token colors).

Text->diagram strengthening:
- references/graphics/text-to-diagram-examples.md: 12 worked sentence->
  skeleton translations incl. the formula/identity boundary and the 額装
  anti-pattern; deck-strategy Step 3b now points hard beats at it.

Verified: 4 palettes x design-lint PASS; icon fixture renders 4 pictograms
at the computed slots; bad icon name -> ICON error + no throw; run-gate
PASS across all 10 themes.
